From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Josh Bailey <josh@vandervecken.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Jun 2026 09:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] log: build nocolor strings before stdout output to fix NULL
 deref (segfault / heap corruption)

log_helper() only builds the non-colorized copies of the prefix/text
(nocolorpre / nocolortxt) when (log_to_file || !log_colorize). The stdout
output branch, however, switches to those non-colorized strings whenever
the default logger is NOT a terminal (stdout redirected to a pipe/file),
regardless of those conditions:

    if (archdep_default_logger_is_terminal() == 0) {
        terminalpre = nocolorpre;   /* may be NULL */
        terminaltxt = nocolortxt;   /* may be NULL */
    }
    log_archdep(terminalpre, terminaltxt);

When log_to_file is off and colorizing is on (the vsiddump.py invocation:
+logtofile +logtostdout, LogColorize defaults to 1) and stdout is a pipe
(every non-interactive run - CI, the headlessvice dump pipeline), both are
still NULL. log_archdep() then does strlen(logtxt) on a NULL pointer, which
reads address 0. Depending on heap/ASLR layout this either segfaults
immediately or corrupts state and crashes later in an unrelated allocation -
i.e. a latent, environment-dependent crash that reproduces reliably only on
some hosts (e.g. the preframr-tokens CI runner). AddressSanitizer pins it
deterministically:

  SEGV ... strlen ... log_archdep src/log.c:615
                      log_helper  src/log.c:767
                      log_printf  src/log.c:903

This was exposed by enabling --enable-cpuhistory (required for the bustrace
per-access hook) only in the sense that the heap layout changed; the defect
is pre-existing in stock VICE log.c and independent of cpuhistory.

Fix: lazily build the non-colorized strings in the stdout branch if they
were not already built, so log_archdep() is never handed a NULL pointer.
logskipcolors() always returns a non-NULL heap string, and the existing
lib_free(nocolorpre)/lib_free(nocolortxt) at the end of log_helper() free
them, so there is no leak.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/log.c | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/log.c b/src/log.c
index aceb5cc5..8e7fe7ee 100644
--- a/src/log.c
+++ b/src/log.c
@@ -760,6 +760,17 @@ static int log_helper(log_t log, unsigned int level, const char *format,
         /* FIXME: we should force colors off here, if the standard logger goes
                   into a file (because stdout was redirected) */
         if (archdep_default_logger_is_terminal() == 0) {
+            /* The non-colorized strings are only built above when log_to_file is
+               set or colorizing is off. When neither holds (e.g. +logtofile with
+               colorizing on) but stdout is not a terminal, they are still NULL
+               here - build them now so log_archdep() never strlen()s a NULL
+               pointer (which segfaults / corrupts the heap). */
+            if (nocolorpre == NULL) {
+                nocolorpre = logskipcolors(pretxt);
+            }
+            if (nocolortxt == NULL) {
+                nocolortxt = logskipcolors(logtxt);
+            }
             terminalpre = nocolorpre;
             terminaltxt = nocolortxt;
         }
